    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I think they are somehow different, queryHook allows you to decide to do or to not do a search given a keypress.\n\nbeforeSearch allows you to modify the search state before it is sent, but you can't cancel the search completely.\n\nIf we make beforeSearch able to decide to not do any request then it would mean that as soon as you use beforeSearch, you wil be responsible for calling helper.search(). That's doable but wonder if it's easier. What do you think?\n",
